CNCP v1 23925
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13755: Parameters of type 'T' cannot be assigned to parameters of type 'UnwrapRefSimple<T>'. ts(2345)",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:16:07.625230+00:00",
  "text": "Parameters of type 'T' cannot be assigned to parameters of type 'UnwrapRefSimple<T>'. ts(2345)\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.18\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```ts\nfunction test<T>() {\n  const list = ref<T[]>([]);\n  const li: T[] = [];\n  list.value.push(...li);\n}\n```\n\n<img width=\"599\" height=\"159\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/74c58dfa-24b9-408c-85d0-cd951e31bd6a\" />\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe type should actually be the same, there should be no errors reported\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe element type within `ref` has an extra layer of `UnwrapRefSimple`, causing an error that prevents inserting the element into the array.\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\n    OS: Windows 11 10.0.26100\n    CPU: (16) x64 AMD Ryzen 9 7940H  w/ Radeon 780M Graphics     \n    Memory: 6.82 GB / 31.22 GB\n  Binaries:\n    Node: 22.17.1 - D:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\node.EXE\n    npm: 10.9.2 - D:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\npm.CMD\n    pnpm: 10.14.0 - D:\\Users\\jcwang\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\pnpm.CMD\n  Browsers:\n    Edge: Chromium (133.0.3065.69)\n    Internet Explorer: 11.0.26100.1882\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nI am unable to distinguish whether it is a problem with Vue or a problem with the Vue language tool. I have submitted two copies [language-tools](https://github.com/vuejs/language-tools/issues/5597)",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
